data.text: @aschiff @Thoughtfulnz @KazemiAlex Despite more boosters and N95 use NZ has more BA2 involved than Australia did at that stage. Might even mean a higher peak is still a fairly probable scenario?
@Thoughtfulnz Here's hoping it's not so high. But also Australoa had less BA2 involved and so even with boosters and more N95 use NZ may peak higher?
@Thoughtfulnz Oh! Wow! I really appreciate your mahi, thank you.
@Thoughtfulnz That makes sense. The trajectories of the states look similar when plotted this way.
@Thoughtfulnz @KazemiAlex Hard to say with that much uncertainty, but I'm a pessimist ... Give it a few more days 😶
@aschiff @KazemiAlex I don't think we quite are, there is a detectable slowdown in increase been happening. And it looks to me a small bit earlier than the AU regions did. https://t.co/UYjTIuSULm
@Thoughtfulnz @KazemiAlex I think that's correct. I had hoped we'd have lower a peak hospital number than those states due to higher booster rates, but looks like we're on a very similar trajectory.
@KazemiAlex census (at least that is my understanding of what the Australian data means by hospitalised, definitely for NZ)
@Thoughtfulnz Is that numbers in hospital beds (census) per timepoint or admissions per day?
